=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.thirdage.com/Games/odibil/odicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: No more levels please!</span><hr size=1> I personally hate the idea of increasing the level cap, even if it only means at the least, 5 levels. I don't have the time or patience left in me to invest in another 5 levels, as I barely have it left in me to get arguably easy AA points.<br>
<br>
If they're going to increase any type of cap, they need to look at other aspects of the game. Whether that means increasing the innate stat caps such as STR, STA, AGI, etc, or increasing skill and combat caps, the last thing I want is 10 more levels.<br>
<br>
It certainly would make anything pre-Luclin insanely trivial, especially Kunark and old world content. Warriors soloing WW dragons, you say? One group taking out Trakanon, eh? It would severely imbalance the game as we know it. Would we have to resort to banishing all 60+ from engaging in combat with certain mobs? Think Naggy and Vox, now imagine all content pre-Luclin the same way. What a joke that would be.<br>
<br>
I believe anything they wish to achieve with the use of more levels can easily be done by the same means of using AA skills. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uodibillauxes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Odibil Lauxes</A> at: 9/9/02 8:19:41 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=archangelranari>Archangel Ranari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(9/9/02 11:13:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=339.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   definitely not</span><hr size=1> At first I was rather excited with the possibility of raising the level cap.  For warriors, that's more hitpoints.  For monks, that's more damage output.  For mages, that's a new pet line of spells!<br>
<br>
However, I knew of a current guild who could take down Ragefire in roughly 9 seconds.  Granted that's Kunark era mobs, I could only imagine what 5 more levels would do to a guild for Velious level mobs.  So in my opinion, I don't think adding 5 more levels would be such a good idea for Verant to do.  As long as a guild is smart and worked hard to be well equipped, they can do anything @ level 60.<br>
<br>
